  "description": "This dataset comprises human electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from 50 subjects viewing 22,248 images representing 1,854 object concepts from the THINGS stimulus database. Participants performed a rapid serial visual presentation task at 10 Hz while concurrently performing an orthogonal fixation color change detection task. The dataset provides neural responses to a large and diverse set of visual stimuli, enabling investigation of object representation in the human brain.",
  "methods_description": "EEG recordings were collected during rapid serial visual presentation of images at 10 Hz. Participants performed an orthogonal fixation color change detection task while viewing the stimuli. Each experimental session lasted approximately 1 hour.",
